* Originally announced as ''Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse (Part One)'',{{cite|ref=true|url= https://deadline.com/2021/12/spider-man-across-the-spider-verse-drops-first-look-trailer-1234885001/|title= ‚ÄòSpider-Man: Across The Spider-Verse‚Äô Drops First-Look Trailer|work= Deadline|last= Choe|first= Brandon|date= December 4, 2021|accessdate= April 23, 2022}} this film later dropped the "Part One" from the title,{{cite|ref=true|url= https://deadline.com/2022/04/spider-man-across-the-spider-verse-summer-2023-theatrical-release-sony-release-date-changes-1235007010/|title= ‚ÄòSpider-Man: Across The Spider-Verse‚Äô Heads To Summer 2023; Sony Dates ‚ÄòEqualizer 3‚Äô Among Other Release Changes|work= Deadline|last= D'Alessandro|first= Anthony|date= April 20, 2022|accessdate= April 21, 2022}} however, the packaging for the Marvel Legends figures for the film still have the "Part One" on the title.
| Trivia                  = * Even before a script was finalized or a villain chosen, the production team had set on ''Across the Spider-Man'' being "a story about family, and the struggle of being both a son and a Spider-Man."{{cite|ref=true|refname=Instagram1|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/CtKGwXCR1BQ/|title=I guess we should start at the beginning. Before we had a script, or...|work=Instagram|first=Patrick|last=O'Keefe|date=June 6, 2023|accessdate=February 2, 2024|archiveurl=https://ghostarchive.org/iarchive/instagram/okeefe_artist/3119335403455729744|archivedate=February 2, 2024}}
* A time-stamp in the security camera in Lenny's bodega places the events of the movie set in [[Earth-1610B]] on 2023/07/11. This contradicts Miles' narration stating that he has been Spider-Man for one year and four months, since the events of {{sl|Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse}} take place in December 2018.
* A set piece from Miles' first fight with the Spot that was cut from the film involved the two characters teleporting through a Chinese restaurant.{{cite|ref=true|refname=Instagram2|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/CthFeqXRd5z/|title=I guess we should start at the beginning. Before we had a script, or|work=Instagram|first=Wendell|last=Dalit|date=June 15, 2023|accessdate=February 2, 2024|archiveurl=https://ghostarchive.org/iarchive/instagram/wendelldalit/3125803713676303987_3125803707837785537|archivedate=February 2, 2024}}
* In a concept-stage version of Miles' talk with Gwen during Jefferson's party saw them at a greenhouse rather than a water tower.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/CtSDM8EyYsR/|title=In another universe, Rio iced Miles‚Äô game in the greenhouse and not the ...|work=Instagram|first=Wendell|last=Dalit|date=June 9, 2023|accessdate=February 2, 2024|archiveurl=https://ghostarchive.org/iarchive/instagram/wendelldalit/3121571574999255825_3121571567206253026|archivedate=February 2, 2024}}
* In a piece of concept art, Miles and Gwen visited Hobie's reality. The aesthetic of Earth-138 was inspired by 1970‚Äôs punk posters, namely the use of overly processed/xeroxed images, cutout shapes, and hand done linework.{{cite|ref=true|refname=Instagram3|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/CtxUnzKP2ar/|title=I guess we should start at the beginning. Before we had a script, or|work=Instagram|first=Dean|last=Gordon|date=June 21, 2023|accessdate=February 2, 2024|archiveurl=https://ghostarchive.org/iarchive/instagram/deangordonart/3130373911921780395_3130373906888585116|archivedate=February 2, 2024}}
* A scene cut from the movie featured Jessica Drew fighting a real cyborg octopus version of Doctor Octopus.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://twitter.com/kristaferanka/status/1683502392757862401|title=Big Wheel Dr Actual Octopus Shocker Beetle Mysterio|work=Twitter|date=24 July, 2023}}
* Alex Ross' Spider-Man design for Sam Raimi's ''[[Spider-Man (2002 film)|Spider-Man]]'' appears in this film in the form of one of the many alternate Spider-Men in the Spider Society.
* The movie features the return of the Spider-Men from several animated series, namely ''[[Spider-Man Unlimited (animated series)|Spider-Man Unlimited]]'', ''[[Spectacular Spider-Man (animated series)|The Spectacular Spider-Man]]'' and ''[[Ultimate Spider-Man (animated series)|Ultimate Spider-Man]]''. ''[[Spider-Man and His Amazing Friends]]'' and the 1994 ''[[Spider-Man (1994 animated series)|Spider-Man]]'' animated series also have presence in the movie in the form of [[Francis Byte (Earth-8107)|Videoman]] making an appearance and [[Peter Parker (Earth-65B)|Earth 65B's Peter Parker]] briefly wearing 1994 Peter's iconic polo shirt, respectively.
* Multiple duplicates of the same Spider-Men appear in the movie, Spider-Man Unlimited being one of the most prominent cases since four different versions of him appeared in different scenes in different locations back to back.
* The following Spider-Man variants were considered but didn't make it into the film: [[Ultimate Spider-Woman]], Ben Reilly as the [[Sensational Spider-Man]], [[Man-Spider]], a [[Peter Parker (Earth-18466)|S.H.I.E.L.D. Spider-Man]], [[Takuya Yamashiro (Earth-51778)|SupaidƒÅman]] and his [[Leopardon]]{{cite|ref=true|url=https://twitter.com/AYMRC/status/1674089548404359171|title=Early freestyle pitch exploration in the Kirbyverse|work=Twitter|date=28 June 2023}}, [[Peter Parker (Earth-2149)|Zombie Spider-Man]], [[Felicia Hardy (Earth-194)|Night-Spider]], [[Peter Parquagh (Earth-311)|Spider-Man 1602]], [[Maybelle Parker (Earth-3123)|Spider-Ma'am]], Spider-Chef, [[Peter Ross (Earth-9602)|Amalgam Universe Spider-Boy]], [[Peter Parker (Earth-Unknown)|Turkish Spider-Man]] from the unlicensed film ''{{WP|3 Dev Adam}}'', [[Peter Parker (Earth-5113)|Dormammuverse Spider-Man]], [[Ashley Barton (Earth-807128)|Ashley Barton]], a robot Spider-Man, a Spider-Wizard, and a fox mascot for Samurai Spider-Man,{{cite|ref=true |url=https://twitter.com/mayday_stan95/status/1661880381518360577 |title=Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse Concept-Arts|work=Twitter|date=25 May 2023}}{{r|Spider-Man: Across the Spider-verse - The Art of the Movie}} and a Toy Biz Spider-Man being held by a giant kid's hand off-screen,{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.empireonline.com/movies/news/across-the-spider-verse-nearly-had-spider-man-toy-held-by-human-hand/|title=Across The Spider-Verse Nearly Included A Spider-Man Toy Being Held By A Giant Human Hand|work=Empire Online|first=Ben|last=Travis|date=April 7, 2023|accessdate=February 2, 2024}}
* Some villains that were considered for the film but didn't make it to the final cut were [[Stilt-Man]], [[Trapster]], [[Wall|The Wall]], [[Agent Venom]], [[Electro]], [[White Rabbit]], [[Jack O'Lantern]], [[Maximus Gargan (Earth-1610B)|Scorpion (Earth-1610B)]], [[Mysterio Avatars|Ultimate Mysterio]], a cavewoman Boomerang, A TV-head Screwball, a few different variants of Green Goblin (a [[Ghost Rider]] Green Goblin, a skier one, a figurine one and a puppet one), [[Ox]], [[Human Fly]], [[Hippo]], [[Xandu]], [[8-Ball]], [[Chtylok]], [[Hammer Harrison]], [[Radioactive Man]], and the fully original character of Coffee Man. Most of the villains were designed for a scene taking place in the [[Bar with No Name]] that was cut from the movie.{{r|Spider-Man: Across the Spider-verse - The Art of the Movie}} Tiger Shark, Clam, and a variant of Diamondhead as prisoners of the Spider Society and another variant of Diamondhead in Earth-138B ultimately made it into the film. The cut scene of the Bar with No Name also featured its proprietor, [[Delilah (Earth-Unknown)|Delilah]], who makes an appearance in ''[[Marvel's Spider-Man 2]]''.<!--pitched ones being Monument Valley variants (Kingpin, Kangaroo, Fly, Mysterio and ig Arachane idk, a Steampunk Vulture and a Wild West Kraven from Web Slinger's universe, Zap comix Kangaroo, Mike Mignola inspired Vulture-->
