* Early in development different styles and characters were explored. These are the sinister six from Norse mythology, and a Kraven in mid 18th century miniature painting style{{cite|ref=true |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Ct7OBoFSmtc/|title=Early in development we were exploring different styles and characters. These are the sinister six from Norse mythology, and a Kraven in mid 18th century miniature painting style.|work=Instagram|first=Jay|last=Thakur|date=June 26, 2023|accessdate=February 2, 2024}}
* The ‚Äúcanon events‚Äù listed are each references to various different Spider-Man stories, most of which happened to the [[Peter Parker (Earth-616)|mainstream variant]] of the character, although many suspiciously did not occur, or have not occurred, in the history of most Spider-Totems. These canon events include the following:
** The death of the Spider-Totem‚Äôs original love interest. This one is unconfirmed, but is alluded to by Gwen when she states that every time Spider-Man and [[Gwen Stacy]] fall in love, [[Amazing Spider-Man Vol 1 121|it doesn‚Äôt end well]]. 
** The Spider-Totem‚Äôs [[Amazing Fantasy Vol 1 15|origin]] of getting superpowers from being bit by a radioactive spider.
** The Spider-Totem receiving an [[Spider-Man (2002 film)|upside-down kiss]].
** The Spider-Totem [[Secret Wars (1984 Event)|bonding]] with the [[Venom (Symbiote)|Venom symbiote]].
** The death of an inspirational figure that teaches the Spider-Totem a variation of ‚Äúwith great power comes great responsibility‚Äù. This tends to be [[Ben Parker]], but for Gwen it is [[Peter Parker (Earth-65B)|Peter Parker]] and for Miles it is [[Aaron Davis (Earth-1610B)|Aaron Davis]].
** The death of a police captain close to Spider-Man (typically [[George Stacy]]) from falling rubble. This event is classified ‚ÄúASM90‚Äù a reference to [[Amazing Spider-Man Vol 1 90|the comic issue]] this took place in within [[Earth-616]].
*** Although Miguel states that the police captain is crushed by rubble trying to save a child, one of the captains shown is George Stacy‚Äôs [[Earth-120703]] [[George Stacy (Earth-120703)|variant]], who was stabbed by the [[Curtis Connors (Earth-120703)|Lizard]] instead of being crushed by rubble, and was simply trying to fight the Lizard as opposed to saving a kid. Arguably, the child was [[Peter Parker (Earth-120703)|his Peter]].
** The Spider-Totem temporarily [[Spider-Man No More!|quitting being a superhero]].
** The Spider-Totem [[Amazing Spider-Man Vol 1 33|pushing themselves out of rubble]].
** The Spider-Totem [[Amazing Spider-Man Annual Vol 1 21|getting married]].
** The Spider-Totem [[Web of Spider-Man Vol 1 32|crawling out of their own grave]].
* The movie features a cameo from {{WP|Metro Boomin}}, who executive-produced the soundtrack to the film, as a version of Spider-Man.
* It is implied that the records of the Spider-Society, in addition to the members themselves, feature various variants of established characters in addition to the established characters themselves. For example, in the records of the canon event detailing the upside-down kiss, [[Peter Parker (Earth-96283)|Peter Parker-96283]] is seen with his upside down kisses with [[Mary Jane Watson|Mary Jane Watson-96823]] and [[Gwendolyne Stacy (Earth-96283)|Gwen Stacy-96283]]. It can be implied that a variant of this Peter ended up in a relationship with Gwen in contrast to the [[Earth-96283]] variant, who is in a relationship with Mary Jane. This could likely explain why some versions of characters, like [[Peter Parker (Earth-751263)|Spider-Man Unlimited]], occasionally have multiple versions of themselves onscreen at the same time.

